<body>

<p class="subtitle">Project Proposal</p>
<h1>Estimating & Project Management Platform</h1>

<p class="meta">
<strong>Prepared For:</strong> K&M Concrete Construction Inc<br>
<strong>Contact:</strong> Andy Kooiker (Owner)<br>
<strong>Date:</strong> October 25, 2023<br>
<strong>Status:</strong> Draft
</p>

<h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
<p class="content">
K&M Concrete Construction Inc requires a dedicated, internal estimating and project management application. The objective is to replace disparate spreadsheets with a single, secure database workflow. This platform will enable estimators to calculate concrete volumes dynamically, track status stages, and maintain a reliable system audit trail.
</p>

<h2>2. Core Features</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Concrete Volume Calculator:</strong> Dynamic calculation of concrete requirements in cubic yards (yd³) based on length, width, and depth parameters, with selectable mix designs.</li>
  <li><strong>Workflow Stage Tracker:</strong> Visual progress pipeline representing stages from Initial Start, Site Prep, and Estimating to Proposal Sent and Scheduling.</li>
  <li><strong>Client Master Data:</strong> A centralized repository of client contacts, site locations, and estimation histories to avoid disconnected record-keeping.</li>
  <li><strong>System Audit Log:</strong> A secure, read-only event trail recording every estimation edit, mix change, and status update for operational accountability.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Proposed Technology Stack</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Next.js (React Framework) with Tailwind CSS for responsive desktop & mobile layout.</li>
  <li><strong>Backend API:</strong> Node.js with Express for scalable business logic processing.</li>
  <li><strong>Database:</strong> PostgreSQL for robust relational structures, transaction safety, and precise audit trails.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Delivery Phases</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Phase 1: Foundation & API (Weeks 1 - 4):</strong> Database schema design, database setup, and core user authentication API modules.</li>
  <li><strong>Phase 2: Estimating & Workflow (Weeks 5 - 8):</strong> Development of the mathematical estimation engine and workflow stage navigation controls.</li>
  <li><strong>Phase 3: Client Portal & Logs (Weeks 9 - 12):</strong> Implementation of client master directories and secure audit logging tracking tables.</li>
  <li><strong>Phase 4: QA & Deployment (Weeks 13 - 16):</strong> Rigorous testing, validation, cloud infrastructure setup, and team onboarding.</li>
</ul>

